<p style="text-align:justify;">his Son One likewise, to Secure his hunt, as his <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[not]</span> power Enough Over him to Secure it for you let <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> ever so willing<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he Only time in which they have any influence is when they get a Keg from their trader, to treat the others with and Can beg plenty of Ammunition &amp; Tobacco to Share amo<span class="AddHand-editors">[ng]</span> them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>hile that lasts, they are great Men, but as Indians in general, have very little Sense of gratitude in their na<span class="AddHand-editors">[ture]</span> when a Chief has nothing to bestow on them, all past <span class="AddHand-editors">[fa]</span>vours are forgot, and his influence is at an End, till he has has it in his power to begin his liberally a New, and I often saw them get a sound Beating from them they were treating all the time, and Some times Worse, getting their Nose bit of, which has been the Case a few Weeks ago with this great English Partison, whose Nose was bit of<span class="AddHand-editors">[f]</span> by his Son in Law, at the Door of what he Calls his Own Fort, and is not yet Cured, but he says that a g<span class="AddHand-editors">[reat]</span> Man like him, must not get Angry, or take any revenge, Especially when he stands in Awe of the person that ill Used him, for there is nothing but an In<span class="AddHand-editors">[dian]</span> will do, Sooner than Own himself to be a Coward<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>hen I was ready, I sent for them, and they were not Lazy</p>

